# Rust
/target
**/*.rs.bk

# Node (flume harness control plane only)
/node_modules

# Flume harness-managed state (not authored, not committed)
/.flume/worktrees/
/.flume/sessions/
/.flume/awake/
/.flume/prior-attempts/

# temper's own surface (`.temper/`) IS committed — surface-authority (`specs/architecture/20-surface.md`).
# It carries the authored `[representation]` layer (`satisfies` + `rationale`) that the
# root `temper.toml` requirements are filled by; those links have no source-side home, so
# committing the surface is what makes the coverage dogfood persistent. Bodies duplicate
# `.claude/`+`specs/` byte-faithfully (the accepted cost); `temper import . --into .temper`
# reconciles bodies while REPRESENTATION-PRESERVE carries the authored layer forward.
